<head>HEM</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">縫邊</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">純／紕</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>MOST OUTER PART of CLOTH OR GARMENT.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for a border in clothing is zhǔn 純.</p>
<p>2. Pí 紕 refers to a trimming.</p>
<p>3. Yì 裔 is a specific term for a border in clothing.</p>
<p>4. Qí 齊 refers to the hem of a mourning cloth.</p>
<p>5. Jī 緝 refers to a trimming.</p>
<p>6. Yuán 緣 refers to a hem in clothing with a bands of fabric applied on it.</p>
<p>7. Rán 袡 is a specific term refering to a hem on the lower part of a cloth.</p>
<p>8. Tuán 褖 specifically refers to a hem of a ritual cloth.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>縫邊</p>
